               <floruit>6thC</floruit>
               <note xml:id="d2e21528" n="42"> On this form see vol.
                                3, under Yohanan (17) B/M, p. 106.
                        </note>
               <note xml:id="d2e21534" n="43"> In Greek
                                – <span xml:lang="checkme"></span> (of the
                                innkeepers). On such designations see Introduction
                            3.1.3.3.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e21544" n="44"> In Syria.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e21558" n="45"> This is an inn inscription. It bears
                                Hebrew names and a biblical quotation (1 Sam 16:4). Yet its
                                tentative date (and the popularity of this name among Christians,
                                see vol. 3, Introduction 1.1.1.2, p. 4-5) puts its Jewish character
                                into question, see vol. 3, Introduction 6.6.7, p. 52. IJO 3, App19 specifically denied the
                                Jewishness of this inscription.</note>
